[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33101] [2812007] [info] Topic: id: 42. html_id: 420000. title: CpanFile
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33109] [2812007] [debug] 	o See also
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33111] [2812007] [debug] 	- [[CPAN]]
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33113] [2812007] [debug] 	- LicenceStuff
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33114] [2812007] [debug] 	- SecurityPolicy
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33121] [2812007] [debug] 	<pre>
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33123] [2812007] [debug] 	The docs here were copied from Google's Gemini, when I asked it how to generate a cpanfile
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33125] [2812007] [debug] 	**1. Manual Creation**
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33126] [2812007] [debug] 	* **Create a file named `cpanfile`:** This file will reside in the root directory of your project.
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33128] [2812007] [debug] 	* **Add dependencies:**
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33129] [2812007] [debug] 	* Each line in the `cpanfile` represents a dependency.
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33131] [2812007] [debug] 	* Use the following syntax: `require 'ModuleName';`
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33132] [2812007] [debug] 	* Example
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33134] [2812007] [debug] 	```perl
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33135] [2812007] [debug] 	require 'JSON';
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33137] [2812007] [debug] 	require 'Template';
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33138] [2812007] [debug] 	require 'DateTime';
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33139] [2812007] [debug] 	require 'DBIx::Class';
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33141] [2812007] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33142] [2812007] [debug] 	**2. Using `Mojolicious::Command::Author::generate::cpanfile`**
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33144] [2812007] [debug] 	* **Install the Mojolicious framework (if not already installed):**
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33145] [2812007] [debug] 	```bash
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33147] [2812007] [debug] 	cpanm Mojolicious
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33148] [2812007] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33150] [2812007] [debug] 	* **Generate the `cpanfile`:**
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33151] [2812007] [debug] 	```bash
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33153] [2812007] [debug] 	mojo generate cpanfile
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33154] [2812007] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33156] [2812007] [debug] 	This command analyzes your Perl source code files (usually located in the `lib` directory) to identify used modules and generates the `cpanfile` accordingly.
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33158] [2812007] [debug] 	**3. Using Carton**
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33159] [2812007] [debug] 	* **Install Carton:**
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33161] [2812007] [debug] 	```bash
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33162] [2812007] [debug] 	cpanm Carton
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33164] [2812007] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33165] [2812007] [debug] 	* **Create a `cpanfile`:**
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33167] [2812007] [debug] 	```bash
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33168] [2812007] [debug] 	carton init
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33170] [2812007] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33171] [2812007] [debug] 	This creates a basic `cpanfile` with some default settings. You can then manually add your project's specific dependencies.
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33173] [2812007] [debug] 	**Key Considerations**
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33174] [2812007] [debug] 	* **Version Constraints:** You can specify version constraints for your dependencies to ensure compatibility and stability. For example
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33176] [2812007] [debug] 	```perl
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33177] [2812007] [debug] 	require 'Module::Name' => '>= 1.2.3';
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33179] [2812007] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33180] [2812007] [debug] 	* **Local Modules:** If you have local modules that are not on CPAN, you can add them to your `cpanfile` using special directives.
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33182] [2812007] [debug] 	* **Testing:** After generating your `cpanfile`, always test your application to ensure all dependencies are installed correctly and your application functions as expected.
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33183] [2812007] [debug] 	**Example `cpanfile`**
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33184] [2812007] [debug] 	```perl
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33186] [2812007] [debug] 	require 'JSON';
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33187] [2812007] [debug] 	require 'Template' => '>= 2.18';
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33189] [2812007] [debug] 	require 'DateTime';
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33190] [2812007] [debug] 	require 'DBIx::Class';
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33191] [2812007] [debug] 	require 'MyLocalModule'; # A hypothetical local module
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33193] [2812007] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33194] [2812007] [debug] 	By using a `cpanfile`, you can easily manage and install the necessary dependencies for your Perl projects, making your development process more efficient and reproducible.
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33196] [2812007] [debug] 	</pre>
[2026-05-28 14:49:48.33200] [2812007] [info] --------------------------------------------------
