[2026-05-28 14:49:50.26054] [2812007] [debug] 	In security, we often assume that foreign/hostile code looks different from legitimate instructions, and we use signatures, patterns, and statistical anomaly detection to detect it. But getting inside someoneâs AI OODA loop uses the systemâs native language. The attack is indistinguishable from normal operation because it is normal operation. The vulnerability isnât a defectâitâs the feature working correctly
