[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11755] [2812007] [debug] 	- TextAnalysisAndFormatting - For Regexp::Grammars
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11762] [2812007] [debug] 	- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Guide/Regular_expressions
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11769] [2812007] [debug] 	- https://perldoc.perl.org/ - PerlDoc
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11775] [2812007] [debug] 	<pre>
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11781] [2812007] [debug] 	>    for (@numbers) {
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11787] [2812007] [debug] 	>       say "$_ is a single-digit number" if m/^\d$/;
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11794] [2812007] [debug] 	>    }
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11800] [2812007] [debug] 	Variant
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11806] [2812007] [debug] 	say "$_ is a single-digit number"
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11812] [2812007] [debug] 	for grep m{\A \d \Z}aax, @numbers;
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11818] [2812007] [debug] 	Also, never forget the aa-modifiers if you want to limit \d to [0-9].
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11826] [2812007] [debug] 	perl -E 'say "\x{0660}\n" =~ /^\d$/'
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11832] [2812007] [debug] 	1
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11838] [2812007] [debug] 	And use \z if the newline is undesired.
[2026-05-28 14:49:54.11846] [2812007] [debug] 	</pre>
